item.title: M25 junctions blocked by Insulate Britain campaigners
item.description: Police make more than 40 arrests at a series of co-ordinated protests around the motorway.

item.title: Met officer admits secretly filming naked women
item.description: Det Insp Neil Corbel hid cameras in tissue boxes, phone chargers and glasses to film his victims.

item.title: Trans man says confusion caused cervix-check delay
item.description: Jamie waited three months for an appointment after an abnormal result - it should be two weeks.

item.title: Four arrested after bodies of two men found in Bristol house
item.description: A murder investigation is launched after the bodies were discovered at a house in Bristol on Sunday.

item.title: Cars welded to make fake BMW dubbed a death trap
item.description: The M3 estate looks flashy - but is a model that has never been made by the car giant, say police.

item.title: Imp decapitation brings early end to arts trail
item.description: Damage to the hand-painted sculptures dotted around Lincoln forces organisers to end the attraction.

item.title: Islington flower seller murder: Man pleads not guilty over Tony Eastlake killing
item.description: James Peppiatt, 21, is accused of attacking Tony Eastlake, his late mother's partner, with a knife.

item.title: Man dies after load falls from crane in Bristol
item.description: A man in his 70s was pronounced dead at the scene, Avon and Somerset Police said.

item.title: Carlisle 'monster' jailed for broken glass rape attempt
item.description: Dean Norman's victim said she feared she was going to be killed and was left feeling "devastated".

item.title: Dorman Long tower listed in emergency to stop demolition
item.description: Hours after a council said it could not block demolition, Historic England listed the tower.

item.title: Bristol Zoo: group battling to stop site becoming housing
item.description: A community group wants to stop the Bristol Zoo site being used for housing after it closes.

item.title: M25 climate protest: Aerials show long traffic queues as junctions blocked
item.description: Climate change protesters are demanding government action on home insulation.

item.title: 'I want the most independence I can get'
item.description: Evie, from Loughborough in Leicestershire, dreams of being a nursery nurse like her mum.

item.title: Emma Raducanu: Young players 'inspired' by her win
item.description: Young tennis players have been inspired by Emma Raducanu, the 18-year-old Grand Slam winner.

item.title: Photographer's images 'like ghosts coming out the mist'
item.description: Guy Bellingham uses a 170-year-old technique to produce striking photos in remarkable detail.

item.title: What it's like to be given a zoo as a gift
item.description: Roughly 40% of the animals at Rutland Zoo come from other rescues.

item.title: New Forest animal deaths: Pony owner calls for speed cameras
item.description: Sarah Weston set up a petition after her four-year-old pony, Juma, was hit and killed in August.

item.title: 'Halo' saved my life - Hamilton relieved after crash
item.description: Lewis Hamilton says Formula 1's 'halo' safety device saved his life in his crash at the Italian Grand Prix.

item.title: Emma Raducanu: US Open champion's mental strength is truly special, says coach
item.description: Andrew Richardson, the coach who guided Emma Raducanu to her astonishing US Open triumph, says her mental strength is "truly special".

item.title: Harvey Elliott: Liverpool teenager suffers serious ankle injury at Leeds
item.description: A visibly upset Jurgen Klopp says Liverpool's Harvey Elliott was in "massive pain" after suffering a serious ankle injury at Leeds.

item.title: Chelsea and Arsenal discover Women's Champions League opponents
item.description: Chelsea face Wolfsburg in the Women's Champions League group stages, with Arsenal in with holders Barcelona.
